Love Amla but not sure how to enjoy it? Try this quick & easy Athela Amla — a Gujarati-style pickled amla that’s tangy, salty, and packed with health benefits! 🌿

This recipe is super simple — no cooking required, just patience while it marinates. 

Comment “Amla” and I will send it to you via DM! 

Here’s how to make it:

1️⃣ Wash Amla in hot water
2️⃣ Rinse and dry completely
3️⃣ Make slits on Amla 
4️⃣ In a clean mason jar, add:
	•	Filtered water
	•	Salt
	•	Turmeric
	•	Lemon juice 🍋
5️⃣ Add the amla and seal the jar
6️⃣ Let it sit for 4–5 days — it gets better as it soaks in the brine! 

Why you should eat more amla:
	•	Boosts immunity
	•	Great source of Vitamin C
	•	Aids digestion
	•	Supports hair & skin health
	•	Naturally detoxifying

Save & Share 💫

Alternatively, you can find the recipe on my blog.

Ever see an item on my IG and wonder if your Costco has it?

🛒 Here’s a Costco shopping hack: Just take the Item # and call your local @costco warehouse. They can look up the product and check if it’s in stock at your local warehouse!

🔥 For example, if you’re looking for the viral Pani Puri give them the item # 1949352
